Emirates NBD 6-Month Market Data Analysis
Project Overview
The project analyzes Emirates NBD stock market data over 6 months. The goal was to understand the stock data metrics and to engineer new metrics to provide insights into the stock, and to compare the metrics using graphs
Key Metrics used
  Columns Used 
    (Open, High, Low, Close, Volume, etc.)
  Metrics Derived 
    Return-(Close Price- Close Price of the day  before)/Close Price of the day before. Used to measure the change 
    Price Volatility: Measuring market "chaos" vs stability. (used the standard deviation function)
    Volume Volatility: Identifying erratic crowd behavior. (used the standard deviation function)
    Breathe (Range %): Visualizing the daily "battle" between buyers and sellers. (high-low/open)x100
    Most interesting metric, range, the logic used behind it, and how it quantifies the behavior of the stock throughout the day 
    Hardest Concepts: Volatility, the standard deviation behind it, took some time to understand, along with some AI assistance 
